    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="818"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that in view of
                    the man; inquiries received at this legation in regard to the possibility of
                    obtaining concessions for the construction and operation of railroads in Persia,
                    I have recently put the question to the grand vizier and was informed by him
                    that an agreement exists between the Persian am Russian Governments whereby no
                    railroads shall be constructed in Persia excepting by Russians or the Russian
                    Government for a period of ten years from the accession of the present Shah.
                    This agreement has seven years still to run, wherefore it will be impossible for
                    air of our citizens to obtain a valid railroad concession until the termination
                    of this period.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lloyd C. Griscom.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
